===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – three mountain peaks. In the Oracle Bone Script, they were represented by triangles rather than vertical strokes. Compare {{zh-l|丘}}, particularly earlier forms.

Unrelated to [[出]] and the top component of [[岁]] and [[豐]]. Also unrelated to [[屮]] and [[巾]].

===Etymology===
Unclear – cognates not known outside Sino-Bai. Cognate with {{cog|bca|svrt||mountain}} < {{cog|sit-bai-pro|*sro⁴}}.

{{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} propose that it is derived from a root {{m|und|*ŋ(ˤ)rar||slope, nearly vertical side}} that also derives {{och-l|巘|gloss=hill|tr=*ŋ(r)ar(ʔ)}}, {{och-l|涯|gloss=river bank|tr=*ŋˤrar}}, {{och-l|顏|gloss=forehead|tr=*C.ŋˤrar}}.

Starostin compares it with {{cog|pdu||sʰôn|mountain}}.

